Fudge Frosting
  --Cook's Country

1 c evaporated milk, divided
1/2 c light brown sugar
8 tbsp unsalted butter, divided
1/2 tsp salt
8 oz chopped bittersweet chocolate
1 tsp vanilla
3 c confectioners' sugar

Heat 1/2 c evaporated milk, 4 tbsp butter, brown sugar, and salt over medium heat until ~25-240F. Transfer to stand mixer fitted with whisk attachment and add 4 tbsp butter and 1/2 c evaporated milk. Mix on low for ~30 s until fully incorporated and butter melted. Let cool to 130F (~15 min). Add chocolate and vanilla and mix on low ~1 min until chocolate is melted. Add confectioners' sugar and mix on low for 3 min. Let cool for 1 hr (80F). When ready to use, mix on medium high until aerated. After frosting cake, refrigerate for 1 hr to set.
